.TH "of_get_dma_window" 9 "of_get_dma_window" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
of_get_dma_window \- Parse *dma-window property and returns 0 if found.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" of_get_dma_window
.BI "(struct device_node *dn "  ","
.BI "const char *prefix "  ","
.BI "int index "  ","
.BI "unsigned long *busno "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t *addr "  ","
.BI "size_t *size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dn" 12
device node
.IP "prefix" 12
prefix for property name if any
.IP "index" 12
index to start to parse
.IP "busno" 12
Returns busno if supported. Otherwise pass NULL
.IP "addr" 12
Returns address that DMA starts
.IP "size" 12
Returns the range that DMA can handle
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This supports different formats flexibly. "prefix" can be
configured if any. "busno" and "index" are optionally
specified. Set 0(or NULL) if not used.
